=C2=A0

True, Dickson=E2=80=99s success at Mattel was also largely about marketing=
=E2=80=94and the Barbie phenomenon proved the
value of the discipline. But turning around a brand like the Gap takes time=
 and talent. The company=E2=80=99s Troye Sivan and Tyla holiday marketing c=
ampaign=E2=80=94which felt like a return to the heart-warming, song-and-dan=
ce-filled campaigns of the =E2=80=9990s=E2=80=94generated $482,000 and $355=
,000, respectively, from their social accounts, according to data from Laun=
chmetrics. Tyla=E2=80=99s Linen Moves campaign generated a total of $1.2 mi=
llion in Media Impact Value in the two weeks after launch. These are stunts=
 for a $9 billion market cap company.

